Gunmen have reportedly killed three persons in an attack on Yadagungume and Limi villages in Ningi Local Government Area (LGA) of Bauchi State. It was learned that one other person was injured in the incident which happened at about 12 am on Wednesday. Punch reports that the victims are identified as; Shuaibu Salihu (17), Ruwa Ali popularly known as Mai Inji (45), and Sunusi Isah Burra. -Advertisement- The gunmen, whose number cannot be ascertained, first attacked Yadagungume and started shooting sporadically, causing panic among the villagers who were already asleep before they attacked Limi village, all in the Burra District of the LGA. The slain victims have been buried this morning in accordance with Islamic rites.